-- Singapore’s Inflation Slowed to Eight-Month Low in January
-- B y   S h a m i m   A d a m
-- 2012-02-23T05:00:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/singapore-s-inflation-slowed-to-eight-month-low-in-january.html
Singapore’s  inflation  slowed to an
eight-month low in January.  The consumer price index rose 4.8 percent in January from a
year earlier, the Department of Statistics said in a statement
today. That was higher than the median estimate of 15 economists
surveyed by Bloomberg News for a 4.7 percent gain. Inflation was
5.5 percent in December, according to previously reported data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shamim Adam in Singapore at 
